comment.author: 55198937@N05
comment._content: 'Helen Nicoll' a 380 gross ton cargo steamer built by Gourlay Bros, Dundee in 1882. Worked in various parts of the Australian trade. Scrapped 1932. See: www.flotilla-australia.com/nicoll.htm

comment._content: Nice photo of a long lived ship, she also played a role in the sinking of the steamship Keilawarra in 1886. www.environment.nsw.gov.au/resources/heritagebranch/marit... Here's an interesting engraving showing the damage to the Helen Nicoll's bow: www.slv.vic.gov.au/miscpics/gid/slv-pic-aab22318 Cheers, Phill
